Semtech LoRa-net
######################

Origin:
    Semtech Lora-net repository
    https://github.com/Lora-net/LoRaMac-node
 
Version:
    4.4.1

Purpose:
    Reference implementation of a LoRa network node
 
Description:
    This code component is used to add Zephyr support for LoRaWAN Specification.
    To speed up the development process it is based on the Semtech LoRa-net.
    The LoRaMAC layer is implemented according to LoRaWAN Specification v1.0.2.
    All LoRaWAN devices implement at least the Class A. 
    The LoRaWAN stack API documentation can be found at: http://stackforce.github.io/LoRaMac-doc/
   
    The following folders are imported:

    LoRaMac-node/src/radio
    LoRaMac-node/src/mac

    LoRaWAN operates in the sub-gigahertz frequency bands and it's specification varies from region 
    to region because of regulatory requirement.LoRaWAN Regions supported:

    EU868 (EU 863-870MHz ISM Band)
    US915 (US 902-928MHz ISM Band)
    CN779 (China 779-787MHz ISM Band)
    EU433 (EU 433MHz ISM Band)
    AU915 (Australia 915-928MHz ISM Band)
    CN470 (CN 470-510MHz Band)
    AS923 (AS923MHz ISM Band)
    KR923 (South Korea 920-923MHz ISM Band)
    IN865 (India 865-867 MHz ISM Band)

   The supported radios are:

    SX1272
    SX1276 
    SX126x

Dependencies:

    This source code depends on ...

URL:
   
   https://github.com/Lora-net/LoRaMac-node

Maintained-by:
   Semtech

License:
